# TanStack Form `form.Subscribe` Selector Pattern

When using `form.Subscribe`, prefer selecting only the needed state keys with a concise object selector.

Preferred canonical shape (from `apps/nextjs/src/components/match/players/selector.tsx`):

```tsx
<form.Subscribe
  selector={(state) => ({
    players: state.values.players,
    teams: state.values.teams,
  })}
>
  {({ players, teams }) => (
    // ...
  )}
</form.Subscribe>
```

Guidance:
- Select only the fields you need from `state`.
- Keep selector output minimal and stable in shape.
- Avoid doing derived computations in the selector; derive inside the child render.
- Use a primitive selector (for example `state.isSubmitting`) only when subscribing to a single scalar value.
